## Executive Summary

The Rider Panel is a **functional but high-risk** real-time delivery management application built with Firebase v8 Realtime Database. It features real-time order streaming, live tracking, a PWA shell, and a glassmorphism UI. However, it suffers from **critical security vulnerabilities** (XSS vectors, permissive Firebase rules, hardcoded secrets), **architectural flaws** (global state pollution, memory leaks, legacy SDK), **accessibility failures** (WCAG AA non-compliant), and **performance issues** (1.4 MB cold payload, oversized icons). The codebase mixes modern patterns (CSS variables, flex/grid) with dangerous practices (inline event handlers, blocking alerts, unsanitized data paths). Immediate remediation required before production use.

