## 5. Firebase Rules Deep Analysis (database.rules.json)

| Path | Read | Write | Validation | Issues |
|------|------|-------|------------|--------|
| `/admins` | **Any auth** ❌ | Admin only ✓ | name & email required | **CRITICAL:** All authenticated users can enumerate admins |
| `/riders` | Self/Admin ✓ | Admin only ✓ | name & email typed | OK |
| `/{outlet}/orders` (list) | **Any auth (status query!)** ❌ | Self/Admin ✓ | total (num), items exist | **CRITICAL:** Query by `status` leaks all orders to any rider |
| `/{outlet}/orders/$id` | Self/Admin/Unassigned ✓ | Self/Admin ✓ | — | OK, but unassigned readable by all authenticated |
| `/bot` | **Any auth** ❌ | **Any auth** ❌ | — | **CRITICAL:** Fully open read/write |
| `/riders/{uid}/notifications` | Inherited self ✓ | Inherited (implicit) | — | **Missing** explicit rules & validation |
| `/waitlist`, `/feedbacks` | Any auth (write) ✓ | Any auth (write, once) ✓ | — | Acceptable for submissions |

**Missing**: `.indexOn` for notification timestamps; no data validation for notifications; no expiration checks.

**Recommendations**
- Restrict `/admins` `.read` to admins/self only
- Remove `query.orderByChild == 'status'` or scope by outlet & role
- Lock `/bot` to admins only
- Add `.validate` for notifications structure

