```

**Step 3:** Use media queries to scale base font on small screens

```css
/* style.css: Add after line 1412 (end of media queries) */
@media (max-width: 480px) {
  :root {
    --base-font-size: 15px; /* Slightly smaller on tiny screens */
  }
}

@media (min-width: 1920px) {
  :root {
    --base-font-size: 18px; /* Larger on 4K */
  }
}
```

**Batch Replace Strategy (Manual + Scripted):**

Since 1,905 lines need conversion, do in passes:

1. Identify all `px` values in typography (font-size, line-height)
2. Identify all `px` in spacing (margin, padding, gap)
3. Identify all `px` in borders (width, radius)
4. Identify all `px` in absolute/relative positioning (top, left, width, height)

**Use `rem` where relative to font-size; keep `px` for hairline borders (1px), shadows.**

**Validation:**
- Browser zoom to 200%: entire UI scales proportionally; no overlapping
- iOS dynamic type: UI respects system font size setting
- Chrome DevTools: Rendering → Emulate CSS media feature `prefers-reduced-motion` → animations stop

