### 5.3 Service Worker Runtime Caching for API

**Problem:** Current SW only caches static assets; API always network.

**Solution:**

```javascript
/* sw.js: Upgrade to stale-while-revalidate for Firebase data */
const CACHE_NAME = 'roshani-rider-v2';

// Runtime caching strategy for database paths (simulate via fetch wrapper)
// Note: Firebase uses XHR, not fetch, so need to intercept differently
// Instead, cache important pages/views

self.addEventListener('fetch', (e) => {
  const url = new URL(e.request.url);
  
  // Cache static assets (already done)
  if (ASSETS.includes(url.pathname)) {
    e.respondWith(caches.match(e.request));
    return;
  }
  
  // For Firebase Realtime Database streaming (long-polling)
  // Skip SW — let it go through network (real-time requirement)
  // But cache initial page loads
  if (e.request.mode === 'navigate') {
    e.respondWith(
      caches.match(e.request).then(cached => {
        return cached || fetch(e.request).then(response => {
          // Cache future navigations (except auth pages)
          if (!url.pathname.includes('/login')) {
            const responseClone = response.clone();
            caches.open(CACHE_NAME).then(cache => cache.put(e.request, responseClone));
          }
          return response;
        });
      })
    );
  }
});
```

**Validation:** Navigate to dashboard second time → instant load from cache while still fetching fresh data in background.

